      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Secretary Monroe of the chamber of\ncommerce is in receipt of an inquiry\nfrom Massachusetts man for farm\nof 1000 to 2000 acres. He wants it near\nSpokane and wants only the finest\nwheat land.\n\n\nThis is only sample of the letters\nthe chamber of commerce is receiving\nevery day. Secretary Monroe is in\ncommunication with colony of Dakota\nfarmers who want to come here.\n\n\nSpecial Agent Cameron, representing\nthe chamber of commerce of Southern,\nOhio, reports the prospects for spring\nImmigration from his district as most\ntiattering\n\n\n\"E'rom the inquiries in our mail and\nthe reports from cur agents\" said\nSecretary Monroe, 1.-THE immigration\nwill be heavier than ever before. The\nnewcomers, to a large extent, are\npeople with money!"
    }
